GET Cisco-IOS-XR-mpls-te-oper:mpls-lcac/soft-preemptions/soft-preemption/{interface-name}/

Retrieve operation of resource: soft-preemption

interface-name: string
in path

ID of interface-name

200 OK
soft-preemption_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  
"soft-preemption": {No description

    
"current-soft-preemption-lsp": [No description

      {
        
"hold-priority": "integer", The path's hold priority

        
"source-address": "string", Source

        
"requested-bandwidth": "integer", The path's requested bandwidth

        
"soft-preempted": "boolean", TRUE is the preemption is a soft preemption

        
"bandwidth-preempted": "boolean", LSPs bandwidth is already preempted

        
"soft-preempted-fr-rrewrite": "boolean", FRR-rewrite is done during soft preemption

        
"destination-address": "string", Destination

        
"soft-preemption-timeout": "integer", If the soft preemption is underway, this value\nindicates the number of seconds before hard\npreemption is triggered

        
"setup-priority": "integer", The path's setup priority

        
"tunnel-id": "integer", Tunnel ID

        
"bandwidth-type": "integer", The path's bandwidth type; 0:BC0, 1:BC1, so on

        
"lsp-id": "integer" LSP ID

      }
    ],
    
"interface-name": "string", Interface name

    
"current-soft-preempted-bandwidth-bc1": "integer", The current BC1 BW that is softly preempted:\nthis is the sum of bandwidth for the LSPs that\nare soft preempted and have not been torn down\nyet

    
"current-soft-preempted-bandwidth-bc0": "integer", The current BC0 BW that is softly preempted:\nthis is the sum of bandwidth for the LSPs that\nare soft preempted and have not been torn down\nyet

    
"total-soft-preempted-bandwidth-bc0": "integer", The total BC0 BW that is softly preempted: this\nis the sum of bandwidth for all the LSPs that\nwere soft preempted

    
"total-soft-preempted-bandwidth-bc1": "integer", The total BC1 BW that is softly preempted: this\nis the sum of bandwidth for all the LSPs that\nwere soft preempted

    
"current-over-subscribed-bandwidth-bc0": "integer", The BC0 bandwidth that is over subscribed on\nthis link: this is the difference between the\nmaximum available BC0 BW on the link and the sum\nof the currently reserved BC0 bandwidth and the\ncurrently soft preempted BC0 BW

    
"current-over-subscribed-bandwidth-bc1": "integer", The BC1 bandwidth that is over subscribed on\nthis link: this is the difference between the\nmaximum available BC1 BW on the link and the sum\nof the currently reserved BC1 bandwidth and the\ncurrently soft preempted BC1 BW

    
"release-soft-preempted-bandwidth-bc1": "integer", The total released BC1 BW that is softly\npreempted: this is the sum of bandwidth for the\nLSPs that are soft preempted and are torn down

    
"link-address": "string", The link's IPv4 address

    
"release-soft-preempted-bandwidth-bc0": "integer" The total released BC0 BW that is softly\npreempted: this is the sum of bandwidth for the\nLSPs that are soft preempted and are torn down

  }
}
